==English==

===Pronunciation===
["krom@%som] or ["krom@%zom] 

===Noun===
A structure in the [[cell]] [[nucleus]] that contains [[DNA]], [[histone]] [[protein]], and other structural proteins.

===Etymology===
19th century: [[Greek]], chrom- ([[colour]]) + sōma ([[body]]), due to the fact that they are stained under [[microscope]].

